BriefingText:
BRIEFING

The Mercury 4 mission is planned as a repeat of MR-3.

You will enter the cockpit 10 minutes before launch.

The goal for today is to insert you into a suborbital trajectory that will take you to an altitude of 187km.
After 4 minutes and 45 seconds, the retrograde engines will fire in retro attitude, before performing an atmospheric reentry.
A drogue and the main chute will reduce your speed after reentry even further, before safely splashing down in the Atlantic.

During the ascent, after cutoff, you will perform a simple FBW Pitch Control System Test, see below Flight Plan for instructions.

Please expect moderate waves at the landing zone.

FLIGHT PLAN
T  -10:00 - Enter cockpit
T +00:00 - Launch
T +02:22 - Tower separation and cutoff
T +03:00 - FBW Pitch Control System Test
T +04:45 - Retro sequence start
T +05:15 - Retrofire

FBW PITCH CONTROL SYSTEM TEST
1) Set flight mode to Fly-By-Wire
2) Pitch down to -34 degrees
3) Set flight mode to ASCS Auto
Goal: Observe if it's possible to modify pitch attitude using FBW.
Description:
The MR-4 was a suborbital mission replicating the MR-3 mission. The Mercury spacecraft was nicknamed the Liberty Bell 7, and it was piloted by the astronaut Virgil "Gus" Grissom. You will enter a ballistic suborbital trajectory and splash down in the Atlantic.

Requirements: Complete Tutorial 1 - 3 in the ACADEMY.

MissionActivities.Description: Perform the manual flight controls test.

Steps.Description: Return to roll 0°, pitch -10° and yaw 0°

MissionActivities.Title: Flight Controls Test

MissionActivities.Description: Attain +14 degrees pitch, 0 roll and 0 yaw initially, and observe Earth through the periscope, modify attitude as required.

Steps.Description: Maneuver to the attitude +14° pitch, 0° yaw and 0° roll
Look down through the periscope, observe the Earth, adjust attitude as needed.

MissionActivities.Title: Earth observation test

9 minutes from launch. Prepare the spaceship for launch.
5 minutes to launch, audible countdown will start 10 seconds before launch.

Loud and clear, José, don't cry too much.
Oke-doke.
OK, it's a nice ride up to now.
Loud and clear.
Roger.
OK. The fuel is go, about {{g}}g's, cabin pressure is coming off the peg, O2 is go, we have {{ampsMainBus}} amps.
Roger. Trajectory looking good.
OK, there - We're starting to pick up a little bit of the noise and vibration. Not bad, though, at all. 50 secs.
OK. The fuel is go, {{g}}g's, cabin is {{cabinPSI}} psi, the O2 is go, {{ampsMainBus}} amps.
Roger.
This is {{capsuleName}}. Fuel is go, {{g}}g, cabin pressure {{cabinPSI}} PSI, and the oxygen is go. The main bus is {{voltMainBus}}. We are go.
Everything is good, cabin pressure holding. 2 minutes and we got {{g}}g's, fuel is go, oxygen is go, {{ampsMainBus}} amps.
Roger, we are go here.
And I see a star!
Stand by for cutoff.
Roger.
There goes the tower.
Roger, there went the tower, affirmative.
Capsule has separated.
Roger, cap. sep. is green.
Oh boy! The sky is very black, the capsule is coming around into orbitital attitude.
Verify squibs are OFF.
Please perform the flight controls test.
Roger, activity over. Go ahead with the Earth observation test.
Roger, please prepare for retro using the checklist.
Roger, preparing for retro.
Retro on my mark, 5, 4, 3, 2, ... 1
Start retro-sequence. Retro-attitude is green.
OK, there's 1 firing, there's 1 firing.
There's 2nd firing, nice little boost.
There goes 3.
All three retros are fired, setting AUTO RETRO JETTISON back to ARM.
Roger, roger
Retro jettison, I do not have a light. I see the straps falling away. I heard a noise. I will use override
Progressing towards re-entry attitude.
Roger
Drag detected, preparing for reentry.
OK. G's are starting to build.
45,000 feet, do you read?
Affirmative. Still reading you. You sound good.
40,000 feet if you read me.
Roger, hearing you loud and clear
35,000 feet
30,000 feet
There's the drogue chute. The periscope has extended.
Roger, understand drogue is good, the periscope is out.
There goes the main chute. Main chute is good, main chute is good, landing bag is green.
{{capsuleName}} this is Atlantic Ship CapCom, our telemetry confirms your events. Over.
Atlantic Ship CapCom, this is {{capsuleName}}.  How do you read me?
Loud and clear, {{capsuleName}}, status looking good.
I'm in the process of putting the pins back in the door at this time.
I can't get one door pin back in. I've tried and tried and I can't get it back in.
Roger, {{capsuleName}}. Card File 23 is heading directly toward you.
Roger.
I'm about 1,500 feet now. The main chute still looks good. There is a small hole in the main chute.
Ah, roger, roger.
Can see the water coming right on up.
Splashdown, powering down.
Roger, pickup on the way. Over, good job.
